"Abstract On 29 January 1992 the EC Commission adopted its proposal for a Directive on the legal protection of databases. At the time of writing, the text has been adopted but not yet revised. Broadly speaking, the proposed Directive will adopt a two-tier approach. It will apply copyright protection to the collection or arrangement of material in electronic databases; and provide the maker of a database with the right to prevent unfair extraction and use of otherwise unprotected material from the database for commercial purposes. The following is an analysis of what is proposed."
